-- Prudential Looks for New London Office, Sunday Telegraph Reports
-- B y   B e n   F a r e y
-- 2012-05-06T11:01:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/prudential-looks-for-new-london-office-sunday-telegraph-reports.html
Prudential Plc has hired Savills Plc
to find it a new headquarters in  London ,  The Sunday Telegraph 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The company is considering the Shard, Heron Tower and the
Walbrook Building as possible offices, the newspaper said, and
is part of a wave of insurance companies looking for new
premises in London.  RSA Insurance Group Plc, Amlin Plc and Jardine Lloyd
Thompson Group Plc are among 13 insurers looking for 1 million
square feet of space, the Telegraph said, citing property agent
CBRE Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Farey in London at 
 bfarey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
